
The Nexus One (codenamed HTC Passion)Photo: The Nexus One, aka HTC Passion, aka Google Phone, has leaked was Google's flagship smartphone manufactured by Taiwan's HTC Corporation. It became available on January 5, 2010 and uses the Android open source mobile operating system.[tpl]cite web|url=http://www.google.com/phone/static/en_US-nexusone_tech_specs.html|accessdate=January 6, 2010|title=Nexus One Phone|publisher=Google[/tpl] [tpl]Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot[/tpl][tpl]cite web|url=http://www.google.com/phone/|accessdate=January 6, 2010|title=Nexus One Phone|work=Google.com|publisher=Google|year=2010[/tpl][tpl]Cite news|first=Rob|last=Jackson|url=http://phandroid.com/2010/01/05/nexus-one-now-available-for-verizonvodafone-too-soon/|accessdate=January 6, 2010|title=Nexus One Now Available...|work=Phandroid|publisher=Phandroid|date=January 5, 2010[/tpl] Features of the phone include the ability to transcribe voice to text,[tpl]Cite news|first=Jason|last=Mick|url=http://www.dailytech.com/An+iPhone+Slayer+Google+Unveils+the+Nexus+One/article17291.htm|accessdate=January 6, 2010|title=Google Unveils the Nexus One, Coming to Verizon in Spring 2010|date=January 5, 2010|newspaper=Daily Tech|publisher=Daily Tech[/tpl][tpl]Cite news|first=Joshua|last=Topolsky|url=http://www.engadget.com/2010/01/04/nexus-one-review/|accessdate=January 6, 2010|title=Nexus One Review|date=January 4, 2010|newspaper=Engadget|publisher=AOL News[/tpl] an additional microphone for dynamic noise suppression,[tpl]cite web|last= Arrington |first= Michael |url= http://www.techcrunch.com/2010/01/05/google-nexus-one-the-techcrunch-review/ |title= Google Nexus One: The TechCrunch Review |publisher= Techcrunch.com |date= 2010-01-05 |accessdate= 2010-01-18[/tpl] and voice guided turn-by-turn navigation to drivers.[tpl]cite web|url=http://www.google.com/googlephone/nexusone-userguide.pdf|format=PDF|accessdate=January 6, 2010|title=Nexus One User Guide|publisher=Google[/tpl][tpl]Cite news|first=Dana|last=Blankenhorn|url=http://blogs.zdnet.com/open-source/?p=5531|accessdate=January 6, 2010|title=Google building a base under Android with Nexus One|date=December 30, 2009|newspaper=ZDNet|publisher=CBS Interactive[/tpl]
The device is sold SIM unlocked (not restricted to use on a single network provider). Google offered T-Mobile USA and AT&T versions of the phone online in the United States before closing the online store in July 2010. A version for use on Vodafone (European) networks was announced on 26 April 2010, available in the UK on 30 April 2010.[tpl]cite web|url=http://www.vodafone.com/start/media_relations/news/local_press_releases/uk_press_releases/2010/nexus_one.html|accessdate=May 1, 2010|title=Google Nexus One Launches on Vodafone UK|publisher=Vodafone|year=2010[/tpl] [tpl]Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot[/tpl] On March 16, 2010, the Nexus One device became available on the Google web store for sale in Canada for use with most Canadian carriers.[tpl]cite web|url=http://googlenexusoneboard.blogspot.com/2010/03/nexus-one-now-compatible-with-at-3g.html|title=Nexus One now compatible with the AT&T 3G network and shipping to Canada|publisher=Google|year=2010[/tpl] In May 2010 Google announced the closing of the web store, with the intention to distribute the phone through partners around the world.Nexus One changes in availability
The bootloader of the phone is unlockable, see below.
